# Code Style Rules

## Modern JavaScript
- Always use modern JavaScript:
  - Avoid to use `require`, always use modern ESM imports instead
  - Use modern Node.js APIs (`fetch`, HTTPS module imports, top level await, etc)
  - Use modern browser APIs and specs, such as:
    - Custom Elements
    - importmaps

## Code Style Settings
- Use following code style settings:
  - Single quotes
  - Use semicolons
  - Avoid to use switch/case statements
  - New lines for key/value pairs in objects
  - New lines for array items

## Code Cleanliness
- Avoid to leave unused imports 
- Avoid to leave unused entity definitions
